# Shared Backend Testing

## Test structure
- Prefer unit tests over integration tests.
- Cover success and failure paths.
- Use multiple-case patterns when they improve clarity and reduce duplication.

## Isolation
- Tests must be deterministic and independent.
- Do not call network or external services in unit tests.
- Avoid shared mutable state across tests.

## Mocking
- Mock external dependencies at the repository boundary only.
- Prefer real implementations over mocks when practical.

## Assertions
- Use clear, specific assertions.
- Cover boundary and edge cases when behavior changes.
